@startuml
title Skeleton Key — patching LSASS to accept a master password

start
:Attacker has SYSTEM on the Domain Controller;
:privilege::debug (acquire debug right on LSASS);
:misc::skeleton\n(patch the LSASS authentication routine in memory);
note right
  In-memory only. The patch does
  NOT survive a reboot of the DC.
end note
:LSASS now accepts a hidden master password
for ANY domain account, alongside the real one;
fork
  :Legitimate user logs in\nwith their real password;
  :Authentication succeeds (unchanged);
fork again
  :Attacker logs in as any user\nwith the master password;
  :Authentication succeeds (backdoor);
end fork
:Defender resets the DC / monitors LSASS\ndebug access to detect and remove it;
stop
@enduml
